<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 4: CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - VALVE
        LEVER REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>VALVE LEVER REMOVAL</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Use the following steps when removing the valve lever assembly from the engine.</para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
            <title>REMOVING VALVE LEVER</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen twelve (12) valve lever adjusting screw nuts (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600422">4.22</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen twelve (12) adjusting screws
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>(
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600422">4.22</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) one (1) full turn.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Loosening valve lever adjusting screws one (1) full turn will avoid possible valve train
                            damage during installation procedure.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove six (6) (long bolts) valve bracket bolt (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600423">4.23</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Shoulder bolt at the rear of the fuel injector
                            <emph type="underscr">DOES NOT</emph>
                            require removal.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1600422" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5152" filename="../figeg5/EG5152.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.22 Loosening Valve Lever Adjusting Screw</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600423" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5157" filename="../figeg5/EG5157.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.23 Removing Valve Lever Assembly Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove valve lever assembly from cylinder head (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600424">4.24</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    )
                    <emph type="bold">.</emph>
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600424" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5158" filename="../figeg5/EG5158.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.24 Removing Valve Lever Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
